<div class=3D"ltx_para" id=3D"S2.SS2.p3">
<p class=3D"ltx_p">One traditional approach for avoiding these difficulties=
 is to make
the <em class=3D"ltx_emph ltx_font_italic">Markov approximation</em>, which=
 leads to a <em class=3D"ltx_emph ltx_font_italic">Markov process</em>
or <em class=3D"ltx_emph ltx_font_italic">Markovian stochastic process</em>=
. According to the Markov approximation,
one assumes that any higher-order conditional probability of the form
<math alttext=3D"p\mathopen{}\mathclose{{\left(i,t|j_{1},t_{1};j_{2},t_{2};=
\dots}}\right)" class=3D"ltx_math_unparsed" display=3D"inline" id=3D"S2.SS2=
