<div class=3D"ltx_para" id=3D"S3.SS3.p3">
<p class=3D"ltx_p">Kraus decompositions play a key role in quantum informat=
ion theory.
They provide (non-unique) generalizations of unitary time evolution
known as <em class=3D"ltx_emph ltx_font_italic">quantum channels</em>, or <=
em class=3D"ltx_emph ltx_font_italic">completely positive trace-preserving =
(CPTP) maps</em>,
that are needed for some kinds of open quantum systems.</p><button class=3D=
"sr-only button" style=3D"display: none;">Report issue for preceding elemen=
t</button>
</div>
</section>
<section class=3D"ltx_subsection" id=3D"S3.SS4">
<h3 class=3D"ltx_title ltx_title_subsection">
<span class=3D"ltx_tag ltx_tag_subsection">3.4 </span>Unistochastic process=
es</h3><button class=3D"sr-only button" style=3D"display: none;">Report iss=
ue for preceding element</button>
<div class=3D"ltx_para" id=3D"S3.SS4.p1">
<p class=3D"ltx_p">The existence of a Kraus decomposition for the time-evol=
ution operator
<math alttext=3D"\Theta\mathopen{}\mathclose{{\left(t\leftarrow 0}}\right)"=
 class=3D"ltx_math_unparsed" display=3D"inline" id=3D"S3.SS4.p1.m1"><semant=
ics><mrow><mi mathvariant=3D"normal">=CE=98</mi><mrow><mi></mi><mrow><mo>(<=
/mo><mi>t</mi><mo stretchy=3D"false">=E2=86=90</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mrow>=
<mo>)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">\Theta\mathopen=
{}\mathclose{{\left(t\leftarrow 0}}\right)</annotation><annotation encoding=
=3D"application/x-llamapun">roman_=CE=98 start_OPEN end_OPEN start_CLOSE ( =
italic_t =E2=86=90 0 end_CLOSE )</annotation></semantics></math> is a cruci=
al new result, and it has
an important corollary. Specifically, if <math alttext=3D"\Theta\mathopen{}=
\mathclose{{\left(t\leftarrow 0}}\right)" class=3D"ltx_math_unparsed" displ=
ay=3D"inline" id=3D"S3.SS4.p1.m2"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=3D"norma=
l">=CE=98</mi><mrow><mi></mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo stretchy=3D"fals=
e">=E2=86=90</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow><annotation encod=
ing=3D"application/x-tex">\Theta\mathopen{}\mathclose{{\left(t\leftarrow 0}=
}\right)</annotation><annotation encoding=3D"application/x-llamapun">roman_=
=CE=98 start_OPEN end_OPEN start_CLOSE ( italic_t =E2=86=90 0 end_CLOSE )</=
annotation></semantics></math>
is not <em class=3D"ltx_emph ltx_font_italic">already</em> a unitary matrix=
, then one can <em class=3D"ltx_emph ltx_font_italic">turn it
