><mi mathvariant=3D"normal">=CE=A3</mi><annotation encoding=3D"application/=
x-tex">\Sigma</annotation><annotation encoding=3D"application/x-llamapun">r=
oman_=CE=A3</annotation></semantics></math>
are guaranteed to be unitary, the formula <math alttext=3D"\Gamma_{ij}\math=
open{}\mathclose{{\left(n\,\delta t+t\leftarrow n\,\delta t}}\right)\equiv|=
(\Sigma^{t/\delta t})_{ij}|^{2}" class=3D"ltx_math_unparsed" display=3D"inl=
ine" id=3D"footnote11.m5"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi mathvariant=3D"normal"=
>=CE=93</mi><mrow><mi>i</mi><mo lspace=3D"0em" rspace=3D"0em">=E2=80=8B</mo=
><mi>j</mi></mrow></msub><mrow><mi></mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>n</mi><mi>=CE=
=B4</mi><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>t</mi><mo stretchy=3D"false">=E2=86=90</mo>=
<mi>n</mi><mi>=CE=B4</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></mrow><mo>)</mo><mo rspace=3D"0e=
m">=E2=89=A1</mo><mo fence=3D"false" rspace=3D"0.167em" stretchy=3D"false">=
