<div class=3D"ltx_para" id=3D"S3.SS4.p10">
<p class=3D"ltx_p">Importantly, one can go in the other direction by expres=
sing any unitary
time-evolution operator <math alttext=3D"U\mathopen{}\mathclose{{\left(t\le=
ftarrow 0}}\right)" class=3D"ltx_math_unparsed" display=3D"inline" id=3D"S3=
.SS4.p10.m1"><semantics><mrow><mi>U</mi><mrow><mi></mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>=
t</mi><mo stretchy=3D"false">=E2=86=90</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mrow><mo>)</m=
o></mrow><annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">U\mathopen{}\mathclose{=
{\left(t\leftarrow 0}}\right)</annotation><annotation encoding=3D"applicati=
on/x-llamapun">italic_U start_OPEN end_OPEN start_CLOSE ( italic_t =E2=86=
=90 0 end_CLOSE )</annotation></semantics></math> in terms
of a time-dependent transition matrix <math alttext=3D"\Gamma\mathopen{}\ma=
thclose{{\left(t\leftarrow 0}}\right)" class=3D"ltx_math_unparsed" display=
=3D"inline" id=3D"S3.SS4.p10.m2"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=3D"normal=
">=CE=93</mi><mrow><mi></mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo stretchy=3D"false=
">=E2=86=90</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow><annotation encodi=
