<div class=3D"ltx_para" id=3D"S3.SS5.p1">
<p class=3D"ltx_p">The appearance of the Schr=C3=B6dinger equation in the p=
revious section
is an important signal that the dictionary (<a class=3D"ltx_ref" href=3D"ht=
tps://arxiv.org/html/2302.10778v3#S3.E15" title=3D"In 3.1 The dictionary =
=E2=80=A3 3 The Stochastic-Quantum Correspondence =E2=80=A3 The Stochastic-=
Quantum Correspondence"><span class=3D"ltx_text ltx_ref_tag">15</span></a>)
is more than just a tool for using Hilbert-space methods to craft
highly general forms of stochastic dynamics. It also suggests that
indivisible stochastic processes have the resources to replicate the
features of quantum theory more broadly.</p><button class=3D"sr-only button=
" style=3D"display: none;">Report issue for preceding element</button>
</div>
<div class=3D"ltx_para" id=3D"S3.SS5.p2">
