tic processes =E2=80=A3 2 Indivisible Stochastic Processes =E2=80=A3 The St=
ochastic-Quantum Correspondence"><span class=3D"ltx_text ltx_ref_tag">2.2</=
span></a>.</p><button class=3D"sr-only button" style=3D"display: none;">Rep=
ort issue for preceding element</button>
</div>
<div class=3D"ltx_para" id=3D"S3.SS6.p4">
<p class=3D"ltx_p">In the Hilbert-space formulation of an indivisible stoch=
astic process,
one can nonetheless assign complex-valued quantities called <em class=3D"lt=
x_emph ltx_font_italic">amplitudes</em>
to the system=E2=80=99s possible trajectories, using the fact that unitary
time-evolution operators <em class=3D"ltx_emph ltx_font_italic">can</em> be=
 composed iteratively, <math alttext=3D"U\mathopen{}\mathclose{{\left(t\lef=
tarrow 0}}\right)=3DU\mathopen{}\mathclose{{\left(t\leftarrow t^{\prime}}}\=
right)U\mathopen{}\mathclose{{\left(t^{\prime}\leftarrow 0}}\right)" class=
=3D"ltx_math_unparsed" display=3D"inline" id=3D"S3.SS6.p4.m1"><semantics><m=
row><mrow><mrow><mi>U</mi><mrow><mi></mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo stre=
tchy=3D"false">=E2=86=90</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>=
